          "properties": {
            "text": {
              "expr": {
                "Literal": {
                  "Value": "'The dashboard identifies planned activities by looking at tasks from the previous month''s data snapshot that were scheduled to finish within the reporting period (between the previous and current data dates) and were not yet marked as complete. To calculate achievement, it tracks these same planned tasks forward to the current month''s data and counts how many have now been marked as \"Complete.\" The completion score represents the percentage of planned activities that were successfully completed, calculated as Achieved divided by Planned. This method ensures that only activities genuinely planned for completion within the period are included in the performance measurement, providing an accurate view of schedule adherence.'"
                }
